# ImageGallery

`TxImageGallery` renders an image thumbnail grid and opens a `TxModal` preview when a thumbnail is clicked. It is best for small gallery sets where every image can be rendered as a thumbnail.

## Basic Usage

::::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ImageGalleryImageGalleryDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  const items = [
    { id: 'one', url: '/images/one.png', name: 'Workspace overview' },
    { id: 'two', url: '/images/two.png', name: 'Release graph' },
  ]
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxImageGallery :items="items" :start-index="1" />
  </template>
