## Composition Examples

### Track Preview Opens

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
function onOpen({ index, item }: { index: number, item: { id: string } }) {
  analytics.track('gallery_open', { index, imageId: item.id })
}
</script>

<template>
  <TxImageGallery :items="images" @open="onOpen" @close="onClose" />
</template>
```

### Controlled Starting Image

```vue
<template>
  <TxImageGallery :items="screenshots" :start-index="selectedIndex" />
</template>
```

`startIndex` is clamped whenever it changes. It chooses the initial/current preview index but does not open the modal by itself.

## Interaction Contract

- The thumbnail grid renders one native `button type="button"` for each item.
- Thumbnail buttons use `aria-label="Open {label} preview"`, where `label` is `item.name` or a generated `Image N` fallback.
- Thumbnail and preview image `alt` text use `item.name`; unnamed images intentionally use empty alt text.
- Empty `items` render no thumbnail buttons and cannot emit `open`.
- Clicking a thumbnail clamps the clicked index, opens the modal, and emits `open` with `{ index, item }`.
- `startIndex` changes are clamped to `0..items.length - 1`.
- When `items` becomes empty, the preview closes and the index resets to `0`.
- Preview navigation is bounded: previous is disabled at the first image, next is disabled at the last image.
- The modal title is the current image name, falling back to `Preview`.
- Close behavior is delegated to `TxModal`; closing emits `close`.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `items` | `ImageGalleryItem[]` | required | Images rendered as thumbnails and previewable modal items. |
| `startIndex` | `number` | `0` | Initial/current preview index, clamped to the available item range. |

### ImageGalleryItem

| Field | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `id` | `string` | Stable key for thumbnail rendering. |
| `url` | `string` | Image URL used by thumbnails and modal preview. |
| `name` | `string` | Optional display name used for labels, alt text, and modal title. |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `open` | `{ index: number, item: ImageGalleryItem }` | Emitted after a thumbnail opens the modal preview. |
| `close` | `void` | Emitted when the modal closes. |

### Slots

No public slots are exposed.

### Exposed Methods

No public instance methods are exposed.

## Best Practices

- Use stable `id` values; do not use array indexes for long-lived gallery data.
- Provide `name` for informative images so button labels, alt text, and modal titles are meaningful.
- Keep the list size modest. This component renders all thumbnails; it is not virtualized.
- Do not pass untrusted remote image URLs without normalizing or proxying them at your application boundary.
- Use `startIndex` for selected preview context, not as a visibility control.
- Use `@open` for analytics or detail-panel coordination; do not mutate `items` synchronously in a way that invalidates the opened image.

## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/image-gallery/src/types.ts`, `TxImageGallery.vue`, and `image-gallery.test.ts`.
- `startIndex` is clamped and updates the current preview index, but it never opens the modal by itself.
- Unnamed images intentionally use empty image alt text while thumbnail buttons still receive generated open labels.

